  "id": "019cdcdc-fd01-7d11-b0d7-9d05029287bb",
  "content": "### Step 7: Commit\n\n## Task 4: LiteStore — QueryableStore with hnsw_rs + Redb\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `crates/corvia-kernel/Cargo.toml` (add hnsw_rs, redb)\n- Create: `crates/corvia-kernel/src/lite_store.rs`\n- Modify: `crates/corvia-kernel/src/lib.rs`\n\nThis is the largest task. LiteStore combines three storage mechanisms:\n- **hnsw_rs** — in-memory HNSW index for vector similarity search, persisted to disk\n- **Redb** — on-disk B-tree for metadata: entry lookup by UUID, scope indexing, ID mapping\n- **Knowledge files** — JSON on disk (from Task 3) for git-tracked source of truth\n\nData flow on `insert`: write JSON file → insert vector into HNSW → write metadata to Redb.\nData flow on `search`: query HNSW → look up UUIDs → load entries → post-filter by scope.\nData flow on `rebuild`: read all JSON files → re-index into HNSW + Redb.\n",
  "source_version": "docs/rfcs/2026-03-01-m1.2-litestore.md",
